cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the privacy concerns in distributed learning systems. It may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses the leakage of private training data. Additionally, the paper involves image classification tasks, which suggests it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of synthetic data and labels also indicates a possible connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the mathematical analysis and empirical evaluation of the proposed approach suggest a potential fit for cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
